modules.description: Provides functions to parse and generate HTTP date strings in the IMF format, converting between OCaml's date/time representations and string literals. Operates on OCaml's `Ptime` type and string values formatted according to RFC 9110. Used to handle HTTP Date headers in web server and client implementations.

Converts HTTP date strings to and from Ptime values using IMF, RFC 850, and obsolete asctime formats. Accepts a century parameter for precise year decoding of RFC 850 dates and supports custom encoding formats. Outputs formatted date strings or prints them to a formatter.
